    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The first phase in the Early Dynastic period in Mesopotamia, from about 2900 to 2750 BCE. It is characterized by innovations in architecture, specific styles of seal carving, and transitional styles in the plastic arts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>La primera fase en el período Dinástico Temprano en Mesopotamia, de aproximadamente 2900 al 2750 a.C. Se caracteriza por innovaciones en arquitectura, estilos específicos de tallado de sellos y estilos de transición en las artes plásticas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De eerste fase van de vroeg-dynastieke periode in Mesopotamië, van circa 2900 tot 2750 v. Chr. Deze wordt gekenmerkt door architectonische vernieuwingen, specifieke stijlen van zegelkunst en overgangsstijlen in de beeldende kunst.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指約自西元前2900年至西元前2750年間，於美索不達米亞發展之早王朝時代的第一個時期。此時期的特色為建築上的創新、特定的印刻風格，以及在造形藝術上的過渡風格。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Première phase de la période dynastique archaïque en Mésopotamie, comprise entre 2900 et 2750 avant notre ère. Elle se caractérise par des innovations architecturales, des styles spécifiques de sculpture de sceaux et des styles transitoires dans les arts plastiques.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>French</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000305/BEINFRAT </Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000115330/BEINFRAT-network (2022)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
